article.headline: Drexel 82, Old Dominion 66
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Sean Brooks scored 22 points to lead Drexel to an 82-66 victory over Old Dominion on Wednesday. Phil Goss added 16 to surpass the 1,000-point mark for his career. Tim Whitworth contributed 14 points for the Dragons (16-8, 11-4 Colonial Athletic Association). Alex Loughton scored 16 points to lead the Monarchs (15-9, 10-5). The Dragons, winners of seven of their last eight, closed the first half on an 18-5 run to take a 43-27 lead into the break. The Dragons shot 55 percent in the opening half while holding Old Dominion to 38 percent, including 0-for-8 from 3-point range. Goss, who finished 4-for-5 from 3-point range, hit three 3s early in the second half as Drexel increased its lead to 64-39 with 12:31 remaining.
